  "notes": "Pernambucano (Recife). Northeastern type. Two strongest north/south isoglosses: (1) NO /t,d/ palatalisation вАФ tia -> [ЋИti…Р], leite -> [ЋИlejt…™] (ALiB: ~10% palatalisation in Recife); (2) open pretonic vowels /e/ -> […Ы], /o/ -> […Ф] (menino -> [m…ЫЋИnin К], boneca -> [b…ФЋИn…Ыk…Р]). Coda /S/ palatalised to [ Г, Т] (Recife chiado). Strong dorsal onset /r/; coda /R/ -> aspiration.",
